headline: These Stocks Moved the Most Today: Warner Bros., Oracle, Micron, Opendoor, Synopsys, Centene, Delta, and More
summary: Stocks soared Thursday as investors shrugged off data showing the consumer price index rose for the fourth month in a row in August, reasoning the Federal Reserve is still likely to cut interest rates at next week’s meeting of its policy committee.  Warner Bros. Discovery  surged 29% after The Wall Street Journal reported that  Paramount Skydance  was prepping a takeover bid.  Oracle  was down 6.2%, a day after shares of the database-software company gained 36% to hit a record high of $328.33.

headline: Centene shares rise after reaffirmed profit forecast, steady Medicare ratings
summary: (Reuters) -Centene shares gained more than 11% in early trading on Thursday after the health insurer reaffirmed its annual profit forecast and said quality ratings for its Medicare plans were in line with expectations.  Preliminary data for Star or quality ratings for Medicare Advantage showed a slightly higher percentage of members in four-star plans, CEO Sarah London shared at the Deutsche Bank Healthcare conference.  The Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services scores health plans between one to five stars, which can influence enrollees' plan choices while increasing government reimbursement levels for higher-rated plans.
